description: Borrowed from Latin occlūdere, from ob (“before”) and claudere (“to shut”).

verbs.description: occlude (third-person singular simple present occludes, present participle occluding, simple past and past participle occluded)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To obstruct, cover, or otherwise block (an opening, a portion of an image, etc.).
(transitive) To absorb, as a gas by a metal.
